      • getFieldByName

        public static Field getFieldByName(Class clazz,
                                   String fieldName)
        Extract a Field from a given class using its name. This method will look into the given class declared fields. If the field is not found, it will then look recursively in all super classes of the given class.
        Parameters:
        clazz - the class to extract the Field from
        fieldName - the name of the field to extract
        Returns:
        the extracted Field, null if not found

        Returns:
